    "comment": "Rationale: Fig 7A: Immunoprecipitation studies indicate that NR2C coprecipitates with SNX27.\nFig 7B: Immunocytochemistry in primary cerebellar neurons shows that SNX27 colocalises with NR2C.\nFig 8A: Immunoblot analysis shows that the level of NR2C was increased by about 35 to 40% in the SNX27-/- brain compared to the wild-type brain.\nFig 8B: Real-time PCR demonstrated that the mRNA levels of NR2C transcripts in brain tissues from wild-type and knockout mice were not significantly different.\nFig 8D: Primary cortical neurons from SNX27+/+ and SNX27-/- mice were transfected with Myc-NR2C and pulse-chased with the anti-Myc antibody for various periods. 85% more NR2C was endocytosed in SNX27+/+ than in SNX27-/- neurons as evidenced by the greater number of internalized NR2C (red puncta) in SNX27+/+ neurons at 5 and 15 min after pulse-chase than in wild-type neurons.. Experimental description: Generation of SNX27-/- mice was performed as described in PMID: 15363411.",
